29 new cases of coronavirus disease have been confirmed by the Kano state government. The confirmation was made by the Kano State Ministry of Health in a tweet via its Twitter handle on Monday. The tweet read “COVID-19 Update as at 12:15am 4th May 2020. “29 new cases of COVID19Kano cases confirmed. “Total confirmed cases in Kano are now 342. “Residents are advised to stay home and stay safe.” Meanwhile, the Nigeria Center for Disease Control, NCDC, on Sunday confirmed 170new cases of coronavirus disease in the country. Nigeria now has 2,558 confirmed cases of COVID-19; 400 patients out of these have been discharged, while 87 deaths have been recorded. Source Twelve new cases of COVID-19 have been confirmed in F.C.T, Abuja. This was disclosed by the Federal Capital Territory Administration in a tweet on Monday. Recall that the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control confirmed 170 new cases on Sunday. The NCDC had said it recorded, “39-Lagos 29-Kano, 24-Ogun, 18-Bauchi, 15-Kaduna,… May 4, 2020 In "News" Kano State Governor, Umar Ganduje, has called for compliance with the lockdown in state two days after asking the Federal Government to ease the restriction, The PUNCH reports. President Buhari had in a nationwide broadcast on Monday ordered a total lockdown in the state as part of measures to curb… May 3, 2020 In "News" The Kano State government has confirmed the death of two more patients who tested positive for coronavirus (COVID-19) in the state. The state Ministry of Health announced this in a tweet, saying that was the situation in Kano as of 12:15pm on Monday. This brings the total number of COVID-19… April 27, 2020 In "Top Stories"